# Coding Style â€” Security & Privacy

## Data Handling
- Do **not** log PII (raw texts, phone, exact usernames) from library code.
- Never store secrets/tokens in code or tests.

## Namespacing
- All Redis keys **must** be prefixed with `SentinelConfig.redis_prefix`.

## Input Validation
- Validate config on init; raise typed exceptions on invalid/empty values.
- Treat external inputs as untrusted; sanitize if used in keys (hash where needed).

## Dependencies
- Optional extras (e.g., `redis`) only imported in specific modules; guard imports with clear error messages.
